::{{DIcon|Arrow}} No, we haven't met before.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108003-->
:::'''Jinyu:''' Then we're strangers &mdash; and I'm relieved. I'm really sorry for bothering you.
:::'''Jinyu:''' ...But we can start to get to know each other now. My name's Jinyu. Nice to meet you.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Have you already forgotten who I am?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108006-->
:::'''Jinyu:''' Ah! We know each other, do we? I'm sorry. I've totally forgotten about you.
:::'''Jinyu:''' Even though we may know each other, let's treat this as us meeting for the first time. My name's Jinyu. Nice to meet you.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502010801_17-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502010801_17-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm (Trailblazer), and the pleasure is all mine.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} ... (Trailblazer).
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} ...
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108012-->
::'''Jinyu:''' You don't wish to tell me your name? I see. Not like that I'll remember it anyway.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502108013-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108013-->
::'''Jinyu:''' Phew... This may be out of the blue, but I'm actually evading the pursuit of my countless ex-lovers. I thought you were one of them, but apparently not.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You have had countless lovers? Such a player!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108015-->
:::'''Jinyu:''' You're mistaken, my heart can only belong to one. When I like someone, it's hard to like another.
:::'''Jinyu:''' But these lovers are from my past reincarnations. I don't know them, but they know me.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} And how do you know I'm not one of them?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108018-->
:::'''Jinyu:''' If you were, you'd surely know what illness has stricken me. But with that sweet, innocent face of yours, I'm certain you have no clue.
:::'''Jinyu:''' If you know what rare illness I have, you would understand very quickly.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502108023-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502108023-->
::'''Jinyu:''' We Vidyadhara usually stay young by molting after living for centuries. Any damage done to the body will be repaired during the molting process, but our memories are completely wiped.
::'''Jinyu:''' As for me and my condition, well, my body compacts this five or six-century process into just one month. After one month, I'd have forgotten about our meeting here and now &mdash; and this love story, too.
::'''Jinyu:''' How about it? Do you understand after hearing me out? I haven't found a lover in this life, and perhaps we're just right for each other.
